19namespace {
20typedef absl::optional<webrtc::SpsParser::SpsState> OptionalSps;
21
22#define RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(x) \
23 if (!(x)) { \
24 return OptionalSps(); \
25 }
26
27constexpr int kScalingDeltaMin = -128;
28constexpr int kScaldingDeltaMax = 127;
29} // namespace
30
31namespace webrtc {
32
33SpsParser::SpsState::SpsState() = default;
34SpsParser::SpsState::SpsState(const SpsState&) = default;
35SpsParser::SpsState::~SpsState() = default;
36
37// General note: this is based off the 02/2014 version of the H.264 standard.
38// You can find it on this page:
39// http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-H.264
40
41// Unpack RBSP and parse SPS state from the supplied buffer.
42absl::optional<SpsParser::SpsState> SpsParser::ParseSps(const uint8_t* data,
43 size_t length) {
44 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(data, length);
45 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
46 return ParseSpsUpToVui(&bit_buffer);
47}
48
49absl::optional<SpsParser::SpsState> SpsParser::ParseSpsUpToVui(
50 rtc::BitBuffer* buffer) {
51 // Now, we need to use a bit buffer to parse through the actual AVC SPS
52 // format. See Section 7.3.2.1.1 ("Sequence parameter set data syntax") of the
53 // H.264 standard for a complete description.
54 // Since we only care about resolution, we ignore the majority of fields, but
55 // we still have to actively parse through a lot of the data, since many of
56 // the fields have variable size.
57 // We're particularly interested in:
58 // chroma_format_idc -> affects crop units
59 // pic_{width,height}_* -> resolution of the frame in macroblocks (16x16).
60 // frame_crop_*_offset -> crop information
61
62 SpsState sps;
63
64 // The golomb values we have to read, not just consume.
65 uint32_t golomb_ignored;
66
67 // chroma_format_idc will be ChromaArrayType if separate_colour_plane_flag is
68 // 0. It defaults to 1, when not specified.
69 uint32_t chroma_format_idc = 1;
70
71 // profile_idc: u(8). We need it to determine if we need to read/skip chroma
72 // formats.
73 uint8_t profile_idc;
74 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadUInt8(profile_idc));
75 // constraint_set0_flag through constraint_set5_flag + reserved_zero_2bits
76 // 1 bit each for the flags + 2 bits = 8 bits = 1 byte.
77 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(1));
78 // level_idc: u(8)
79 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBytes(1));
80 // seq_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
81 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(sps.id));
82 sps.separate_colour_plane_flag = 0;
83 // See if profile_idc has chroma format information.
84 if (profile_idc == 100 || profile_idc == 110 || profile_idc == 122 ||
85 profile_idc == 244 || profile_idc == 44 || profile_idc == 83 ||
86 profile_idc == 86 || profile_idc == 118 || profile_idc == 128 ||
87 profile_idc == 138 || profile_idc == 139 || profile_idc == 134) {
88 // chroma_format_idc: ue(v)
89 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(chroma_format_idc));
90 if (chroma_format_idc == 3) {
91 // separate_colour_plane_flag: u(1)
92 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(1, sps.separate_colour_plane_flag));
93 }
94 // bit_depth_luma_minus8: ue(v)
95 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
96 // bit_depth_chroma_minus8: ue(v)
97 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
98 // qpprime_y_zero_transform_bypass_flag: u(1)
99 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
100 // seq_scaling_matrix_present_flag: u(1)
101 uint32_t seq_scaling_matrix_present_flag;
102 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(1, seq_scaling_matrix_present_flag));
103 if (seq_scaling_matrix_present_flag) {
104 // Process the scaling lists just enough to be able to properly
105 // skip over them, so we can still read the resolution on streams
106 // where this is included.
107 int scaling_list_count = (chroma_format_idc == 3 ? 12 : 8);
108 for (int i = 0; i < scaling_list_count; ++i) {
109 // seq_scaling_list_present_flag[i] : u(1)
110 uint32_t seq_scaling_list_present_flags;
111 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
112 buffer->ReadBits(1, seq_scaling_list_present_flags));
113 if (seq_scaling_list_present_flags != 0) {
114 int last_scale = 8;
115 int next_scale = 8;
116 int size_of_scaling_list = i < 6 ? 16 : 64;
117 for (int j = 0; j < size_of_scaling_list; j++) {
118 if (next_scale != 0) {
119 int32_t delta_scale;
120 // delta_scale: se(v)
121 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
122 buffer->ReadSignedExponentialGolomb(delta_scale));
123 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(delta_scale >= kScalingDeltaMin &&
124 delta_scale <= kScaldingDeltaMax);
125 next_scale = (last_scale + delta_scale + 256) % 256;
126 }
127 if (next_scale != 0)
128 last_scale = next_scale;
129 }
130 }
131 }
132 }
133 }
134 // log2_max_frame_num and log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb are used with
135 // BitBuffer::ReadBits, which can read at most 32 bits at a time. We also have
136 // to avoid overflow when adding 4 to the on-wire golomb value, e.g., for evil
137 // input data, ReadExponentialGolomb might return 0xfffc.
138 const uint32_t kMaxLog2Minus4 = 32 - 4;
139
140 // log2_max_frame_num_minus4: ue(v)
141 uint32_t log2_max_frame_num_minus4;
142 if (!buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(log2_max_frame_num_minus4) ||
143 log2_max_frame_num_minus4 > kMaxLog2Minus4) {
144 return OptionalSps();
145 }
146 sps.log2_max_frame_num = log2_max_frame_num_minus4 + 4;
147
148 // pic_order_cnt_type: ue(v)
149 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(sps.pic_order_cnt_type));
150 if (sps.pic_order_cnt_type == 0) {
151 // log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb_minus4: ue(v)
152 uint32_t log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb_minus4;
153 if (!buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb_minus4) ||
154 log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb_minus4 > kMaxLog2Minus4) {
155 return OptionalSps();
156 }
157 sps.log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb = log2_max_pic_order_cnt_lsb_minus4 + 4;
158 } else if (sps.pic_order_cnt_type == 1) {
159 // delta_pic_order_always_zero_flag: u(1)
160 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
161 buffer->ReadBits(1, sps.delta_pic_order_always_zero_flag));
162 // offset_for_non_ref_pic: se(v)
163 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
164 // offset_for_top_to_bottom_field: se(v)
165 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
166 // num_ref_frames_in_pic_order_cnt_cycle: ue(v)
167 uint32_t num_ref_frames_in_pic_order_cnt_cycle;
168 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
169 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(num_ref_frames_in_pic_order_cnt_cycle));
170 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_ref_frames_in_pic_order_cnt_cycle; ++i) {
171 // offset_for_ref_frame[i]: se(v)
172 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
173 }
174 }
175 // max_num_ref_frames: ue(v)
176 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(sps.max_num_ref_frames));
177 // gaps_in_frame_num_value_allowed_flag: u(1)
178 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
179 //
180 // IMPORTANT ONES! Now we're getting to resolution. First we read the pic
181 // width/height in macroblocks (16x16), which gives us the base resolution,
182 // and then we continue on until we hit the frame crop offsets, which are used
183 // to signify resolutions that aren't multiples of 16.
184 //
185 // pic_width_in_mbs_minus1: ue(v)
186 uint32_t pic_width_in_mbs_minus1;
187 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(pic_width_in_mbs_minus1));
188 // pic_height_in_map_units_minus1: ue(v)
189 uint32_t pic_height_in_map_units_minus1;
190 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
191 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(pic_height_in_map_units_minus1));
192 // frame_mbs_only_flag: u(1)
193 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(1, sps.frame_mbs_only_flag));
194 if (!sps.frame_mbs_only_flag) {
195 // mb_adaptive_frame_field_flag: u(1)
196 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
197 }
198 // direct_8x8_inference_flag: u(1)
199 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ConsumeBits(1));
200 //
201 // MORE IMPORTANT ONES! Now we're at the frame crop information.
202 //
203 // frame_cropping_flag: u(1)
204 uint32_t frame_cropping_flag;
205 uint32_t frame_crop_left_offset = 0;
206 uint32_t frame_crop_right_offset = 0;
207 uint32_t frame_crop_top_offset = 0;
208 uint32_t frame_crop_bottom_offset = 0;
209 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(1, frame_cropping_flag));
210 if (frame_cropping_flag) {
211 // frame_crop_{left, right, top, bottom}_offset: ue(v)
212 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(frame_crop_left_offset));
213 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
214 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(frame_crop_right_offset));
215 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(frame_crop_top_offset));
216 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
217 buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(frame_crop_bottom_offset));
218 }
219 // vui_parameters_present_flag: u(1)
220 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(buffer->ReadBits(1, sps.vui_params_present));
221
222 // Far enough! We don't use the rest of the SPS.
223
224 // Start with the resolution determined by the pic_width/pic_height fields.
225 sps.width = 16 * (pic_width_in_mbs_minus1 + 1);
226 sps.height =
227 16 * (2 - sps.frame_mbs_only_flag) * (pic_height_in_map_units_minus1 + 1);
228
229 // Figure out the crop units in pixels. That's based on the chroma format's
230 // sampling, which is indicated by chroma_format_idc.
231 if (sps.separate_colour_plane_flag || chroma_format_idc == 0) {
232 frame_crop_bottom_offset *= (2 - sps.frame_mbs_only_flag);
233 frame_crop_top_offset *= (2 - sps.frame_mbs_only_flag);
234 } else if (!sps.separate_colour_plane_flag && chroma_format_idc > 0) {
235 // Width multipliers for formats 1 (4:2:0) and 2 (4:2:2).
236 if (chroma_format_idc == 1 || chroma_format_idc == 2) {
237 frame_crop_left_offset *= 2;
238 frame_crop_right_offset *= 2;
239 }
240 // Height multipliers for format 1 (4:2:0).
241 if (chroma_format_idc == 1) {
242 frame_crop_top_offset *= 2;
243 frame_crop_bottom_offset *= 2;
244 }
245 }
246 // Subtract the crop for each dimension.
247 sps.width -= (frame_crop_left_offset + frame_crop_right_offset);
248 sps.height -= (frame_crop_top_offset + frame_crop_bottom_offset);
249
250 return OptionalSps(sps);
251}
